 Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Roydon II was born in 1452, in East Peckham, Kent, England, his father, Sor Robert Royden 3rd Baron of Roydon Haule, was 20 and his mother, Lady Cecily Inglethorpe Baroness Of Reydon, was 18. He married Lady Jane Johanna Clifton about 1474, in Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. He died on 15 May 1487, in Kent, England, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1452–15 May 1487":"1452–15. mai 1487","1452–1487":"1452–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","–1505":"–1505","1456–1526":"1456–1526","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1477–1525":"1477–1525","1487–Female":"1487–Surnud","1432–1468":"1432–1468","1434–1476":"1434–1476","1451":"1451","15 May 1487":"15. mai 1487","1480":"1480","1525":"1525","1468":"1468","1434":"1434","1456":"1456","1477":"1477","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1432":"1432","1487":"1487","20 May 1476":"20. mai 1476","1475":"1475","1452":"1452","about 1475":"umbes 1475","about 1487":"umbes 1487","about 1474":"umbes 1474","1505":"1505","1526":"1526","Roydon Hall, Kent, England":"Kent, England","England":"England","East Peckham, Kent, England":"East Peckham, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Royden Haule Manor, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1452–15 May 1487":"1452–15. toukokuuta 1487","1452–1487":"1452–1487","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","–1505":"–1505","1456–1526":"1456–1526","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut","1477–1525":"1477–1525","1487–Female":"1487–Kuollut","1432–1468":"1432–1468","1434–1476":"1434–1476","1451":"1451","15 May 1487":"15. toukokuuta 1487","1480":"1480","1525":"1525","1468":"1468","1434":"1434","1456":"1456","1477":"1477","1455":"1455","1476":"1476","1432":"1432","1487":"1487","20 May 1476":"20. toukokuuta 1476","1475":"1475","1452":